<TITLE> Govt to boost missions for better expat services: FM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 18 (bdnews24.com)Foreign minister Dipu Moni has said the government would boost staff in its overseas missions to provide better services to expatriates. Bangladeshis expatriates in Rome met with the foreign minister Tuesday, said a foreign ministry statement Wednesday They informed her of problems that include obstacles in sending remittances to Bangladesh. "The foreign minister said the government would take necessary measures to increase its manpower in Bangladesh's embassies and missions across the world to provide better services to expatriate Bangladeshis," said the foreign ministry statement. Dipu Moni also said her government was thinking of opening a consulate office in Milan, it said. She said the government would examine the possibility of setting up some branches of state-owned banks in Rome or in other Italian cities. Bangladeshi workers abroad often allege that the officials at Bangladesh missions do not provide adequate support services. Foreign ministry officials say manpower of all missions is currently fixed in line with the organogram adopted in 1982 when Bangladesh had only six lakh people overseas. The number Bangladeshis living and working abroad has jumped to around 65 lakh.
